05:06.002 --> 05:07.378
Hi, Jack.

05:10.535 --> 05:11.608
It's me, Bridget.

05:12.959 --> 05:14.011
You know.

05:14.013 --> 05:16.050
Yeah, yeah, hi.

05:16.052 --> 05:17.993
I saw you playing.

05:17.995 --> 05:19.145
It sounded really good.

05:20.291 --> 05:22.427
Thanks, thanks a lot, appreciate it.

05:22.793 --> 05:25.128
It's good to see you're still playing.

05:27.925 --> 05:30.035
What else have you been up to these days?

05:31.765 --> 05:34.546
Just stuff, things, you know.

05:34.548 --> 05:36.046
That's great.

05:36.463 --> 05:39.148
You know it really is good to see you.

05:41.935 --> 05:43.768
What's it been, 10 years now?

05:45.882 --> 05:47.632
Sounds about right.

05:48.885 --> 05:50.628
Well I'm sure you have some stories.

05:53.020 --> 05:53.853
A few.

05:56.543 --> 06:00.300
Well um, you know we
should grab dinner sometime,

06:00.302 --> 06:01.133
you know, catch up.

06:01.135 --> 06:04.225
Yeah, we should,
absolutely, sounds great.

06:05.503 --> 06:07.345
Well, what are you doing tonight?

06:11.866 --> 06:13.616
We're having lasagna.

06:46.222 --> 06:47.093
Just give me a few minutes.

06:47.095 --> 06:49.580
I gotta give the husband the 411.

06:49.582 --> 06:52.196
You can go ahead and park behind me.

06:52.198 --> 06:53.031
Okay.

07:17.393 --> 07:19.893
What the fuck am I doing here?

07:28.385 --> 07:31.810
Oh, Jesus Christ, holy shit.

07:34.377 --> 07:36.076
She's married, no big deal.

07:36.078 --> 07:37.661
She's just married.

08:04.138 --> 08:05.221
All righty.

08:29.240 --> 08:32.073
So how do you two know each other?

08:35.083 --> 08:35.917
We were in school together.

08:35.926 --> 08:36.759
I told you about it.

08:38.015 --> 08:40.043
I don't remember a Jack.

08:40.044 --> 08:41.847
Honey, I've mentioned him.

08:46.163 --> 08:48.246
Well, how did you meet?

08:49.245 --> 08:51.743
Mrs. Sullivan's class, third grade.

08:51.745 --> 08:53.593
Good year.

08:53.595 --> 08:55.443
Taught us how to write in cursive.

08:55.445 --> 08:57.782
Turns out they don't
really do that anymore.

08:57.784 --> 08:59.463
I'm not really sure why that is.

08:59.465 --> 09:02.465
We didn't really get to know
each other until high school.

09:03.415 --> 09:05.893
Freshman year, first game of the season.

09:05.895 --> 09:06.795
Football player?

09:08.035 --> 09:09.663
Drums and percussion.

09:09.665 --> 09:11.776
Musician, man of my own heart.

09:11.778 --> 09:13.124
Oh, you play?

09:13.126 --> 09:14.418
I dabble.

09:15.685 --> 09:17.483
Our football team wasn't too good,

09:17.485 --> 09:20.418
so most of the time Jack
and I just mess around.

09:22.726 --> 09:25.482
I take it you
were in the marching band.

09:25.484 --> 09:26.613
I was.

09:26.615 --> 09:27.743
Three and a half years.

09:27.745 --> 09:29.563
How did you manage the half?

09:29.565 --> 09:31.423
I decided to dedicate some of my time

09:31.425 --> 09:33.475
to some other extracurricular activities.

09:35.926 --> 09:37.308
I took a semester of art.

09:38.230 --> 09:39.063
Ah.

09:42.015 --> 09:43.803
Wait, you hate football.

09:43.805 --> 09:45.843
Why were you at the
game in the first place?

09:45.845 --> 09:47.767
Were you in marching band too?

09:47.769 --> 09:50.698
No, I was a cheerleader.

09:55.535 --> 09:56.368
Really?

09:57.385 --> 09:58.218
No.

09:59.555 --> 10:00.633
Yeah?

10:00.635 --> 10:02.558
Yeah, I was a cheerleader.

10:05.775 --> 10:06.673
Wow.

10:06.675 --> 10:08.598
I didn't realize you had the, uh,

10:10.617 --> 10:12.673
the, what word am I looking for?

10:12.675 --> 10:14.318
Coordination, you know?

10:15.265 --> 10:17.343
She was actually the head cheerleader.

10:17.345 --> 10:18.176
Really?

10:18.178 --> 10:19.948
The girl could move.

10:26.095 --> 10:28.663
So what is it you do, Jack?

10:28.665 --> 10:29.498
Meaning?

10:30.345 --> 10:34.058
Like work, what's your career?

10:35.195 --> 10:36.028
I play.

10:38.041 --> 10:38.968
You still banging away?

10:40.215 --> 10:42.638
Not as much as I'd
like to but yes, I bang.

10:45.775 --> 10:47.213
Well when's your next show?

10:47.215 --> 10:50.561
I know we'd love to come out and see you,

10:50.563 --> 10:52.438
see you banging away
at the drums, you know.

10:53.539 --> 10:55.281
And wouldn't that be great, sweetheart?

10:55.283 --> 10:57.493
Yeah, it would be.

10:57.495 --> 10:59.843
I'm actually between gigs right now.

10:59.845 --> 11:01.201
But I'll be sure to let you both know

11:01.203 --> 11:02.453
when I'm back on my feet.

11:04.505 --> 11:05.338
Yeah.

11:08.099 --> 11:09.783
I mean it must be tough, you know,

11:09.785 --> 11:10.753
keeping up with the business

11:10.755 --> 11:13.748
and consistently finding work.

11:20.755 --> 11:22.679
So who have you played with?

11:22.681 --> 11:24.228
What have you done?

11:25.902 --> 11:28.538
Uh, a few big name acts.

11:29.595 --> 11:30.795
Subbed in a tour or two.

11:32.695 --> 11:35.445
I've worked with a lot of up
and coming talent actually.

11:36.295 --> 11:37.919
Most of which stalled out,

11:37.921 --> 11:40.028
but it's a process.

11:41.422 --> 11:44.038
Right, well I'm sure
you're very talented.

11:45.145 --> 11:47.358
Like I said, between gigs.

11:58.925 --> 12:02.435
Ooh, sorry this is
work, I gotta take it.

12:30.795 --> 12:34.283
I'm sorry to cut the evening
short but that was work.

12:34.285 --> 12:35.253
They need me out on the first flight

12:35.255 --> 12:36.143
out to Seattle.

12:36.145 --> 12:37.307
Tonight?

12:37.309 --> 12:38.608
I'm sorry.

12:40.575 --> 12:41.924
This guy gets it.

12:41.926 --> 12:44.084
If Phil Collins needed
a replacement drummer,

12:44.086 --> 12:46.888
he'd be halfway around
the world, you know?

12:52.835 --> 12:56.688
I'll be back in two days, okay?

12:58.115 --> 13:00.650
Jack, it was great meeting you.

13:00.652 --> 13:01.488
You too.

13:04.145 --> 13:06.228
I'll be just a minute.

13:15.867 --> 13:16.700
Fuck.

13:22.785 --> 13:23.618
Fuck.

13:26.963 --> 13:29.633
So, what's in Seattle?

13:29.635 --> 13:31.553
Uh the Freeman deal might fall through.

13:31.555 --> 13:33.748
They want me to do damage control.

13:34.865 --> 13:36.483
They need you in Seattle for that?

13:36.485 --> 13:38.993
I mean, I don't know
what you want me to do.

13:38.995 --> 13:42.208
You know, they call me
like this every so often.

13:43.249 --> 13:45.253
Oh my God, these fucking drawers,

13:45.255 --> 13:46.948
can we get a new thing please?

13:52.555 --> 13:55.364
Is he still downstairs by himself?

13:55.366 --> 13:57.433
Oh, come on, he's fine.

13:57.435 --> 13:59.473
Look, Bridge, I know you knew the guy

13:59.475 --> 14:01.213
like a decade ago.

14:01.215 --> 14:02.313
Paul, come on.

14:02.315 --> 14:04.543
He's fine, I know him.

14:04.545 --> 14:07.053
No, you knew him, that's what that is.

14:07.055 --> 14:11.193
You haven't seen him in like 10 years.

14:11.195 --> 14:12.693
He's not fine.

14:12.695 --> 14:14.573
Look at him, he looks like Charles Manson.

14:14.575 --> 14:16.273
Oh my god.

14:16.275 --> 14:17.503
When's the last time he had a shower?

14:17.505 --> 14:19.305
I smelled him from across the table.

14:21.585 --> 14:23.081
So judgemental.

14:55.245 --> 14:56.645
Have you seen my passport?

14:58.565 --> 14:59.398
No.

15:10.165 --> 15:10.996
See what I mean?

15:10.998 --> 15:13.333
- These fucking drawers.
- Fucking drawers.

15:13.335 --> 15:15.552
Ah, thank you.

15:16.299 --> 15:17.308
He's living out of a car.

15:19.675 --> 15:22.275
What the hell were you
thinking inviting him here?

15:24.505 --> 15:27.712
Am I the only one that's
sane in this relationship?

15:27.714 --> 15:30.583
He's a good guy.

15:30.585 --> 15:31.523
That's not fine.

15:31.525 --> 15:33.013
Good guy, I don't care what he is.

15:33.015 --> 15:35.323
He's homeless living out of his car.

15:35.325 --> 15:37.413
Why are you bringing him into our home?

15:37.415 --> 15:39.015
What the hell were you thinking?

15:39.975 --> 15:42.325
Why do you need a
passport to go to Seattle?

15:43.895 --> 15:46.263
Look, I gotta go.

15:46.265 --> 15:48.493
I'm already late for my flight.

15:48.495 --> 15:49.628
Get him out of here.

15:52.725 --> 15:55.209
Homeless, what?

15:55.211 --> 15:56.798
He cannot stay.

16:09.015 --> 16:11.231
Jack, it was an absolute
pleasure to meet you.

16:11.233 --> 16:12.064
Oh.

16:12.066 --> 16:13.413
You too, Paul.

16:13.415 --> 16:15.369
Hopefully we can
do this again sometime.

16:15.371 --> 16:16.204
Absolutely.

16:24.198 --> 16:25.029
I need to get going.

16:25.031 --> 16:26.448
Okay.

16:30.896 --> 16:31.727
Would you like some more wine?

16:31.729 --> 16:33.728
No, thanks.

16:34.705 --> 16:35.538
Thank you.

16:36.438 --> 16:37.956
Actually, I should probably get going.

16:37.958 --> 16:40.291
What, no, no, not already.

16:41.355 --> 16:42.913
It was great seeing you.

16:42.915 --> 16:44.628
I really appreciate the meal.

16:46.665 --> 16:48.393
After all this time, that's it?

16:48.395 --> 16:52.328
Just a slice of lasagna
and a few glasses of wine?

16:54.655 --> 16:56.228
Come on, just one more drink.

16:58.474 --> 17:00.852
Well.

17:00.854 --> 17:01.937
I don't know.

17:02.891 --> 17:05.103
I wouldn't want to drink all your wine.

17:05.105 --> 17:06.068
I'm in a club.

17:24.765 --> 17:27.647
So, Jacky boy.

17:28.535 --> 17:30.853
Where have you been all my life?

17:30.855 --> 17:32.528
You know, around.

17:34.545 --> 17:36.303
What are the odds that
we run into each other

17:36.305 --> 17:37.468
after all this time?

17:38.655 --> 17:41.183
Well, statistically speaking I'd say

17:41.185 --> 17:43.293
most of our high school class
still lives in this town

17:43.295 --> 17:47.788
so eh, like 70-30 maybe?

18:02.238 --> 18:04.003
Did you ever call?

18:04.005 --> 18:04.838
Excuse me?

18:05.785 --> 18:07.728
Me, did you ever call me?

18:10.565 --> 18:12.638
I mean, I tried.

18:15.325 --> 18:16.975
What does that mean, you tried?

18:20.039 --> 18:22.833
There was one night where I called you

18:22.835 --> 18:24.678
over and over again.

18:25.775 --> 18:26.925
But you never answered.

18:28.455 --> 18:29.983
You were probably at a party

18:29.985 --> 18:31.133
or studying in the library.

18:31.135 --> 18:32.983
Massive orgy.

18:32.985 --> 18:34.883
It was always a massive orgy

18:34.885 --> 18:36.483
or a gangbang up at school.

18:37.263 --> 18:40.098
Okay, those things sound fun too.

18:46.745 --> 18:47.578
Sorry.

18:48.555 --> 18:51.213
I just, I didn't want to be a burden

18:51.215 --> 18:53.365
and it seemed like a
good idea at the time.

18:55.631 --> 18:57.265
I just wanted you to be happy.

19:01.377 --> 19:03.018
Well, mission accomplished.

19:17.150 --> 19:19.293
So how much does one have to make

19:19.295 --> 19:21.945
in order to afford a television
with a curved screen?

19:25.635 --> 19:28.953
That is one of Paul's toys.

19:28.955 --> 19:30.708
He loves his toys.

19:31.886 --> 19:32.717
And what does he do?

19:32.719 --> 19:34.363
With me?

19:34.365 --> 19:35.524
For money.

19:35.526 --> 19:38.163
Oh, he's in finance.

19:38.165 --> 19:41.503
He's a consultant for some
pretty high end clients.

19:41.505 --> 19:44.283
Hence him being called
away from his loving wife

19:44.285 --> 19:46.193
in the middle of the night.

19:46.195 --> 19:47.895
And he finds the money worth it?

19:49.882 --> 19:52.283
It's a beautiful television.

19:52.285 --> 19:55.300
It's a great picture from
anywhere in the house.

19:55.302 --> 19:56.135
I bet.

19:59.929 --> 20:02.263
So how did you two get together?

20:02.265 --> 20:03.682
What's the story?

20:07.595 --> 20:10.195
We're gonna need something
much stronger for that.

20:11.105 --> 20:11.938
Okay.

20:15.655 --> 20:16.620
Lead the way.

20:16.622 --> 20:18.455
All right.

20:19.332 --> 20:22.493
You know, the more you
build up anticipation,

20:22.495 --> 20:26.289
it just, it hurts, so maybe
you should tell the story.

20:27.575 --> 20:28.663
I'm sorry.

20:28.665 --> 20:31.028
I'm just trying to find my courage.

20:32.734 --> 20:34.768
Is it hidden within the vodka?

20:36.215 --> 20:37.048
Well.

20:40.945 --> 20:42.743
You know, I'm not too sure.

20:42.745 --> 20:45.743
But I will look for it.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.348
You're certainly
doing a very thorough check.

20:50.805 --> 20:52.713
Okay, okay, okay.

20:52.715 --> 20:56.578
So the story of me and Paul.

20:57.725 --> 21:00.583
It was my junior year and I just finished

21:00.585 --> 21:03.323
my last finals, so me and
a bunch of my girlfriends

21:03.325 --> 21:04.333
are going to the city.

21:04.335 --> 21:05.838
You know, drinks and a show.

21:07.195 --> 21:08.045
Theater?

21:10.455 --> 21:12.593
I was never really the theater type.

21:12.595 --> 21:15.428
We were looking for rock, something loud.

21:16.670 --> 21:18.238
Ooh, girl of my own heart.

21:20.270 --> 21:22.243
So anyway we ended up in this

21:22.245 --> 21:24.873
rundown dive bar, you know, the ones

21:24.875 --> 21:26.748
that the hipsters turn
into an organic tea bar

21:26.750 --> 21:28.308
five years later.

21:29.585 --> 21:31.923
Anyway, it was taco Tuesday.

21:31.925 --> 21:36.613
So we were devouring tacos
and downing margaritas

21:36.615 --> 21:39.083
like the tequila fountain was dry.

21:39.085 --> 21:41.111
How's the vodka fountain doing?

21:42.725 --> 21:43.675
That's answers my question.

21:46.454 --> 21:48.183
Go on, go on.

21:48.185 --> 21:49.533
Well.

21:49.535 --> 21:53.073
As we were enjoying our
little slices of heaven

21:53.075 --> 21:56.723
these yuppies from Wall Street came up

21:56.725 --> 21:58.453
and for lack of a better term

21:58.455 --> 22:00.663
were trying to spit game.

22:00.665 --> 22:01.708
What'd they say?

22:02.691 --> 22:05.433
That I can't really recall.

22:05.435 --> 22:07.063
Blacked out?

22:07.065 --> 22:10.373
No, they had had spicy tuna rolls

22:10.375 --> 22:12.903
from that sushi bar across the street.

22:12.905 --> 22:14.813
And their breaths collectively smelled

22:14.815 --> 22:18.348
like fish, tuna and spicy mustard.

22:18.350 --> 22:19.968
Ew, potent.

22:22.285 --> 22:23.883
He was like a knight.

22:23.885 --> 22:26.093
Gallant, brave.

22:26.095 --> 22:28.188
Did he challenge them to a duel?

22:28.190 --> 22:30.233
Um, no.

22:30.235 --> 22:32.950
He pretended to be my lover.

22:32.952 --> 22:33.823
Ugh.

22:33.825 --> 22:36.748
But it was enough to
scare the yuppies off.

22:37.685 --> 22:39.868
Then he bought me my fourth margarita.

22:42.227 --> 22:44.133
What was it called?

22:44.135 --> 22:44.966
What, where we met?

22:44.968 --> 22:46.730
Yeah, the bar, what was it called?

22:46.732 --> 22:48.083
Uh, the Alibi Room.

22:48.085 --> 22:49.447
No shit.

22:49.449 --> 22:50.280
What?

22:50.282 --> 22:51.423
I played there.

22:51.425 --> 22:53.240
You played at the Alibi Room?

22:53.242 --> 22:54.713
Yeah yeah, absolutely.

22:54.715 --> 22:55.883
When were you there?

22:55.885 --> 22:57.380
What was the day?

22:57.382 --> 23:01.908
Uh, June 29th I think?

23:03.265 --> 23:05.679
You're joking, you're playing with me.

23:05.681 --> 23:06.512
You're pulling my leg, right?

23:06.514 --> 23:07.475
Why would you say that?

23:08.555 --> 23:09.388
Ah.

23:10.450 --> 23:13.166
I was there the day before.

23:13.168 --> 23:14.893
On the 28th I was there.

23:14.895 --> 23:15.945
That's when I played.

23:16.785 --> 23:17.616
That year?

23:17.618 --> 23:19.775
Yeah, that year, if
I'm doing my math right.

23:21.752 --> 23:22.585
Fuck.

23:24.445 --> 23:27.448
You're right, definitely need
something stronger for this.

23:31.665 --> 23:33.115
I should probably stop though

23:33.839 --> 23:35.663
before I'm too drunk to drive.

23:36.196 --> 23:39.013
I think
you're already past that.

23:39.015 --> 23:42.093
I'm quite happy to say
that I'm very capable

23:42.095 --> 23:43.145
of holding my liquor.

23:44.565 --> 23:45.398
In my mouth.

23:50.425 --> 23:53.738
So um, where are you staying these days?

23:56.855 --> 23:58.005
You know where.

23:59.425 --> 24:00.275
Stay.

24:01.225 --> 24:02.088
I can't stay.

24:03.330 --> 24:04.178
Why not?

24:05.355 --> 24:06.648
You know why not.

24:08.005 --> 24:09.633
Give me one reason.

24:09.635 --> 24:11.228
The night is young.

24:15.748 --> 24:16.912
Oh my god.

24:18.692 --> 24:20.873
You're very convincing.

24:20.875 --> 24:21.713
Very, very good.

24:21.715 --> 24:24.290
I know.

24:24.292 --> 24:25.702
The night is young.

24:28.647 --> 24:29.803
Oh god.

24:29.805 --> 24:30.638
Okay.

24:32.825 --> 24:35.078
Bartender, more wine!

24:44.655 --> 24:46.328
Nothing could beat this.

24:49.633 --> 24:50.983
The quiet calmness of home.

24:54.215 --> 24:55.508
Remember prom night?

24:57.925 --> 24:58.878
Under the stars?

25:00.075 --> 25:01.243
Yeah.

25:01.245 --> 25:03.023
You were so nervous that night

25:03.025 --> 25:06.033
you puked in the bushes
before you rang the doorbell.

25:06.035 --> 25:06.925
You saw that?

25:07.852 --> 25:09.509
Oh no.

25:09.511 --> 25:10.342
So, wow.

25:10.344 --> 25:11.177
Oh my God.

25:13.873 --> 25:15.433
What an odd night.

25:15.435 --> 25:16.268
Which part?

25:17.245 --> 25:19.115
The DJ that kept playing EDM

25:20.732 --> 25:22.543
or the stale salad and dry chicken

25:22.545 --> 25:23.868
they served us for dinner?

25:25.212 --> 25:26.863
I'd say the whole fiasco

25:26.865 --> 25:29.303
if we were being completely honest.

25:29.305 --> 25:30.953
Absolutely.

25:30.955 --> 25:32.605
Afterward wasn't so bad though.

25:33.865 --> 25:35.913
All we needed was a blanket and the waves

25:35.915 --> 25:36.908
to help us sleep.

25:40.405 --> 25:43.349
Well, if we're being completely honest,

25:43.351 --> 25:45.823
I think you should know,

25:45.825 --> 25:47.618
I was never intending us sleeping.

25:49.045 --> 25:52.783
That I knew.

25:52.785 --> 25:54.143
You've always been very observant.

25:54.145 --> 25:56.229
I tell everyone that.

25:56.231 --> 25:57.231
Everyone on the street.

26:08.924 --> 26:10.538
Is that another one of Paul's toys?

26:12.495 --> 26:14.518
No, that one's mine.

26:16.295 --> 26:17.453
It's kind of late in the season

26:17.455 --> 26:20.767
but if you wanna go swimming,

26:20.769 --> 26:23.208
we could borrow some of Paul's trunks.

26:29.655 --> 26:30.605
What are you doing?

26:33.975 --> 26:35.503
Nothing.

