52:29.425 --> 52:32.318
Well, we have a more
pressing matter at hand.

52:34.265 --> 52:36.238
I'm not gonna drink this shit anymore.

52:37.681 --> 52:39.218
Because it's gonna make me puke.

52:39.220 --> 52:40.888
Okay, sorry.

52:43.545 --> 52:44.673
Simple solution.

52:44.675 --> 52:47.163
How about we switch back to vodka?

52:47.165 --> 52:48.708
Okay, that sounds good, right?

52:48.744 --> 52:49.577
Sure.

52:50.265 --> 52:53.545
And that rug over there is calling to me

52:55.145 --> 52:58.138
to go and pass out and just relax.

52:59.217 --> 53:00.768
I've had enough of the games.

53:01.878 --> 53:03.628
All right, sounds good.

53:04.655 --> 53:06.355
I can't wait for you to join me.

54:14.776 --> 54:15.858
So you went into marketing.

54:17.035 --> 54:18.348
Just like you always wanted.

54:20.295 --> 54:21.278
Sort of.

54:22.785 --> 54:24.585
Sort of, what do you mean sort of?

54:26.055 --> 54:29.628
Just, I wish I was a
little further along by now.

54:31.742 --> 54:33.513
I did work on one ad campaign though.

54:33.515 --> 54:34.715
Yeah, what was it for?

54:35.585 --> 54:37.793
I don't think you'd know.

54:37.795 --> 54:38.813
Why not?

54:38.815 --> 54:40.178
I got television in my car.

54:42.339 --> 54:43.420
I'm just kidding.

54:43.422 --> 54:44.977
I barely have working FM radio.

54:49.038 --> 54:50.183
No really, what was it?

54:50.185 --> 54:52.198
It's called Volcano Chips.

54:53.155 --> 54:54.763
Hey is that the one with the guy

54:54.765 --> 54:57.438
who's drinking water on
the floor next to the dog?

54:58.625 --> 54:59.553
Yeah.

54:59.555 --> 55:01.199
That is the one.

55:01.201 --> 55:02.201
I loved that song.

55:03.195 --> 55:06.913
That jingle is fantastic, it's so 80s.

55:06.915 --> 55:10.358
Wait, wait, what's the way they sing?

55:10.360 --> 55:14.300
♪ A flavor eruption right in your mouth ♪

55:14.302 --> 55:18.973
♪ A spicy treat that's hot as hell ♪

55:18.975 --> 55:22.300
♪ Volcano Chips, they're
a scorching treat ♪

55:22.302 --> 55:24.993
♪ So get some today, and feel the heat ♪

55:24.995 --> 55:26.803
Volcano Chips, get some today

55:26.805 --> 55:29.958
before time and supplies run out!

55:31.585 --> 55:32.535
They're going fast.

55:33.725 --> 55:35.048
So fast.

55:37.545 --> 55:41.133
Oh my god, that was a really
popular commercial, wasn't it?

55:41.135 --> 55:43.173
Yeah, it was.

55:43.175 --> 55:44.173
Wait, if it was so successful,

55:44.175 --> 55:45.725
why didn't you get another one?

55:47.455 --> 55:48.873
Career politics.

55:48.875 --> 55:50.298
Oh, fuck that.

55:51.763 --> 55:53.733
No, I'm writing them a letter.

55:53.735 --> 55:55.688
Several letters and I'm demanding more.

55:57.005 --> 55:58.961
I might even sing for them.

55:58.963 --> 56:01.183
Please, don't do that.

56:01.185 --> 56:02.418
You'll get me fired.

56:03.425 --> 56:05.898
I'm a drummer and
singing is not my forte.

56:07.025 --> 56:08.138
Yeah, but,

56:09.379 --> 56:11.563
it's still cute when you do.

56:11.565 --> 56:14.817
You know, I still have the tape.

56:14.819 --> 56:15.652
No you don't, no.

56:16.563 --> 56:17.453
I do.

56:17.455 --> 56:19.243
Nah, mmm-mmm, impossible.

56:19.245 --> 56:21.238
No way, I burned them all.

56:23.139 --> 56:23.972
No.

56:42.975 --> 56:44.780
♪ I'm out of my mind you can see ♪

56:44.782 --> 56:47.238
♪ I need a padded white
cell for my lunacy ♪

56:47.240 --> 56:52.240
♪ 'cause I'm crazy about you babe ♪

56:52.400 --> 56:54.380
♪ A nice straight jacket
keeps me restrained ♪

56:54.382 --> 56:57.100
♪ The thought of you
is driving me insane ♪

56:57.102 --> 56:59.857
♪ You know one thing that I need ♪

56:59.859 --> 57:01.368
Now that's not so bad, is it?

57:02.382 --> 57:04.049
It's excruciating.

57:05.478 --> 57:07.580
It's still the sweetest thing

57:07.582 --> 57:09.606
anyone's ever done for me.

57:09.608 --> 57:11.512
Well, no one ever said I was bright.

57:19.032 --> 57:22.108
♪ Pull me Together. Straigten
me up make me all better. ♪

57:22.110 --> 57:24.572
♪ Give me a chance, give me a sign ♪

57:24.574 --> 57:27.089
♪ Give me your love, I'll be all right ♪

57:27.091 --> 57:28.508
♪ I'm out of my head ♪

57:28.510 --> 57:29.544
♪ You are the answer ♪

57:29.546 --> 57:31.948
♪ The remedy to make me feel better ♪

57:31.950 --> 57:35.532
♪ The one thing that I had ♪

57:35.534 --> 57:38.367
♪ For my sanity ♪

57:41.054 --> 57:43.814
You know, you really
have a great life here.

57:43.816 --> 57:45.354
Do I?

57:45.356 --> 57:47.216
You know you do.

57:47.218 --> 57:48.818
Paul is one lucky guy.

57:49.955 --> 57:52.342
You know we really don't
have to talk about him.

57:53.715 --> 57:55.798
He's part of your life.

57:57.022 --> 57:57.855
I mean,

58:00.259 --> 58:02.103
look at all this.

58:02.105 --> 58:03.953
He built something I've only dreamt about

58:03.955 --> 58:07.228
and here it is, he has it.

58:08.725 --> 58:10.713
He has you, so

58:10.715 --> 58:11.865
yeah he's pretty lucky.

58:15.145 --> 58:15.978
Well um,

58:17.245 --> 58:19.648
sometimes there's more to life than luck.

58:20.744 --> 58:22.416
I wouldn't know about that.

58:22.418 --> 58:26.021
I haven't been doing too
great in that department

58:26.023 --> 58:28.300
as of late.

58:28.302 --> 58:29.681
Well we found each other.

58:29.683 --> 58:32.502
That's pretty lucky, right?

58:32.504 --> 58:33.523
Yeah.

58:33.525 --> 58:35.008
A little too lucky.

58:36.605 --> 58:38.140
Have you been following me?

58:40.045 --> 58:42.813
Yep, and I have a white
van right outside too

58:42.815 --> 58:43.993
filled with candy.

58:43.995 --> 58:44.826
Wonderful.

58:44.828 --> 58:46.068
My own personal stalker.

58:51.085 --> 58:52.843
Oh, I have an idea.

58:52.845 --> 58:53.678
Come with me.

59:00.062 --> 59:03.881
You're not gonna show me
that white van, are you?

59:12.835 --> 59:15.335
Most of this stuff hasn't
been touched in years.

59:17.755 --> 59:21.693
Paul went through a
little phase in college.

59:21.695 --> 59:23.945
Guess he never really
completely got over it.

59:35.475 --> 59:37.138
I am so sorry.

59:39.295 --> 59:40.268
Jackie!

59:41.785 --> 59:42.618
Wanna play me?

59:44.645 --> 59:46.543
That's kind of an odd request.

59:46.545 --> 59:47.495
I meant pool.

59:50.542 --> 59:51.679
Sure.

59:54.955 --> 59:56.078
Not too shabby.

59:57.339 --> 01:00:00.660
Well, I haven't played since college.

01:00:00.662 --> 01:00:02.959
Oh wait, I didn't go.

01:00:02.961 --> 01:00:04.836
I learned in bars, like real men do.

01:00:06.838 --> 01:00:08.756
All right, we'll get this right here.

01:00:08.758 --> 01:00:09.591
Excuse me.

01:00:12.854 --> 01:00:13.687
Oh shit.

01:00:24.589 --> 01:00:25.888
All right, so pitch me.

01:00:25.890 --> 01:00:28.674
Tell me some commercials, I wanna hear it.

01:00:28.676 --> 01:00:30.473
All right.

01:00:30.475 --> 01:00:32.833
So there's this guy, right?

01:00:32.835 --> 01:00:34.983
And he's having a nightmare.

01:00:34.985 --> 01:00:37.663
And all of his soda cans are empty.

01:00:37.665 --> 01:00:39.123
And he's searching and searching

01:00:39.125 --> 01:00:41.163
and the footage is getting
crazier and crazier

01:00:41.165 --> 01:00:42.533
and then bam!

01:00:42.535 --> 01:00:45.203
He wakes up, all is good,

01:00:45.205 --> 01:00:48.038
he's in his bed, when
his girlfriend walks in.

01:00:49.795 --> 01:00:53.215
She says, "All our soda's missing".

01:00:54.674 --> 01:00:56.873
Okay, all right.

01:00:56.875 --> 01:00:58.235
And?

01:00:58.237 --> 01:00:59.070
And...

01:01:03.195 --> 01:01:04.028
He's like.

01:01:07.435 --> 01:01:08.485
That's really good.

01:01:09.772 --> 01:01:11.754
I don't even like soda that much

01:01:11.756 --> 01:01:13.056
and now I really want one.

01:01:14.058 --> 01:01:16.594
Well I guess that means
I'm doing my job then.

01:01:16.596 --> 01:01:19.846
You know, if they decide to pick it up.

01:01:21.375 --> 01:01:22.856
If not, maybe you should just go around

01:01:22.858 --> 01:01:24.296
to everyone, one by one,

01:01:24.298 --> 01:01:26.152
tell them the pitch.

01:01:26.154 --> 01:01:28.712
And then, once they see
the increase in sales,

01:01:28.714 --> 01:01:30.223
the big wigs that run your firm

01:01:30.225 --> 01:01:31.338
will finally cash in.

01:01:32.935 --> 01:01:34.618
Wouldn't that be a nice change of pace?

01:01:37.738 --> 01:01:41.453
♪ Hear me now ♪

01:01:41.455 --> 01:01:43.096
♪ If you want the truth of it ♪

01:01:43.098 --> 01:01:47.592
♪ My tongue has been tide in regret ♪

01:01:47.594 --> 01:01:50.312
♪ Hear and now I gotta make this right ♪

01:01:50.314 --> 01:01:51.773
Why don't you do some spec work?

01:01:51.775 --> 01:01:53.633
Reach out to companies independently?

01:01:53.635 --> 01:01:55.192
It's not that easy.

01:01:55.194 --> 01:01:56.312
Why not?

01:01:56.314 --> 01:01:57.578
I have a contract.

01:01:59.065 --> 01:02:00.003
Break it.

01:02:00.005 --> 01:02:01.608
And why would I do that?

01:02:02.735 --> 01:02:04.511
Well to be fair,

01:02:04.513 --> 01:02:06.103
sounds like a pretty shitty contract

01:02:06.105 --> 01:02:08.328
if they're not developing
any of your ideas.

01:02:09.590 --> 01:02:10.508
That's a good point.

01:02:11.635 --> 01:02:15.108
Maybe we can write something together.

01:02:15.110 --> 01:02:16.963
You know, change their minds.

01:02:16.965 --> 01:02:18.245
Like what?

01:02:18.247 --> 01:02:19.793
A drummer powered by soup?

01:02:19.795 --> 01:02:20.768
I mean, why not?

01:02:21.875 --> 01:02:23.003
I'm sure you can write something better

01:02:23.005 --> 01:02:25.082
than Volcano Chips.

01:02:25.084 --> 01:02:27.167
Now that's a challenge.

01:02:30.826 --> 01:02:35.684
♪ Here and now ♪

01:02:35.686 --> 01:02:39.519
♪ We've gotta make this right ♪

01:02:42.904 --> 01:02:45.404
Hold on, my phone's ringing.

01:02:47.175 --> 01:02:48.008
It's Paul.

01:02:49.459 --> 01:02:52.116
Just give me a second, okay?

01:02:52.118 --> 01:02:54.951
♪ Just say it to me ♪

01:03:01.078 --> 01:03:02.143
Hey hon.

01:03:02.145 --> 01:03:03.073
Hey yeah, thanks for answering.

01:03:03.075 --> 01:03:04.474
How was your flight?

01:03:04.476 --> 01:03:05.553
It was good.

01:03:05.555 --> 01:03:06.773
Is the weather nice?

01:03:06.775 --> 01:03:08.138
It's Seattle.

01:03:08.140 --> 01:03:09.473
It was mediocre.

01:03:10.838 --> 01:03:15.098
But hey, is he still there?

01:03:31.777 --> 01:03:34.239
I get like this weird
feeling from you that

01:03:34.241 --> 01:03:36.196
you have still some sort
of connection with him

01:03:36.198 --> 01:03:37.519
that you're,

01:03:37.521 --> 01:03:38.998
what's that noise?

01:03:39.000 --> 01:03:40.917
Is he playing my drums?

01:03:48.577 --> 01:03:49.479
You don't, and you don't
even have an answer,

01:03:49.481 --> 01:03:51.397
that's like the best part, I get it, like.

01:03:51.399 --> 01:03:52.597
I gotta go.

01:03:52.599 --> 01:03:53.935
And make sure he's gone.

01:03:53.937 --> 01:03:55.354
Seriously, make...

01:04:26.015 --> 01:04:27.678
Still got that magic touch.

01:04:29.575 --> 01:04:30.408
Thanks.

01:04:32.325 --> 01:04:33.158
How's Paul?

01:04:34.265 --> 01:04:35.228
He's uh,

01:04:38.081 --> 01:04:41.113
god, I just remember sitting
there in that auditorium

01:04:41.115 --> 01:04:42.908
just watching you.

01:04:44.583 --> 01:04:46.013
What are you talking about?

01:04:46.015 --> 01:04:48.263
Oh you know, that
battle of the bands thing

01:04:48.265 --> 01:04:49.098
you guys did.

01:04:50.375 --> 01:04:51.743
Yeah, yeah.

01:04:51.745 --> 01:04:54.268
Everyone else just
drowned out, you know.

01:04:55.404 --> 01:04:57.533
I could just see how much you loved it.

01:04:57.535 --> 01:04:59.353
Right, we were kids.

01:04:59.355 --> 01:05:00.348
It was a battle.

01:05:01.223 --> 01:05:02.803
It was fun.

01:05:02.805 --> 01:05:05.873
Yeah, but, those other guys

01:05:05.875 --> 01:05:07.138
were never gonna last.

01:05:08.898 --> 01:05:09.898
I know, I knew it.

01:05:11.481 --> 01:05:13.258
You play when you can play.

01:05:13.260 --> 01:05:14.778
Yeah, I guess.

01:05:16.895 --> 01:05:19.718
When I didn't hear from you at school,

01:05:21.065 --> 01:05:23.165
I always kind of wished you'd given it up.

01:05:24.945 --> 01:05:25.778
Why?

01:05:28.380 --> 01:05:30.730
'Cause then maybe I
would have still had you.

01:05:35.623 --> 01:05:37.706
Why are you doing this?

01:05:38.985 --> 01:05:40.048
Why am I here?

01:05:43.239 --> 01:05:45.523
I saw you at that park.

01:05:45.525 --> 01:05:48.953
For so many years I wondered,

01:05:48.955 --> 01:05:50.613
what would I say?

01:05:50.615 --> 01:05:52.518
What would I do if I saw you?

01:05:55.205 --> 01:05:57.392
You deserve a second chance.

01:05:59.639 --> 01:06:01.863
A second chance at what?

01:06:01.865 --> 01:06:03.637
You live in a car.

01:06:03.639 --> 01:06:04.472
So what?

01:06:05.719 --> 01:06:07.795
What, a second chance at what?

01:06:07.797 --> 01:06:09.763
Plan B.

01:06:09.765 --> 01:06:12.473
You know, to get your life right again.

01:06:12.475 --> 01:06:13.868
I got my life right.

01:06:15.180 --> 01:06:16.673
You know I might not have this life

01:06:16.675 --> 01:06:17.506
or my own bedroom,

01:06:17.508 --> 01:06:20.215
but at least I went after what I wanted.

01:06:22.359 --> 01:06:24.158
How does it feel to
slowly lose who you are?

01:06:26.335 --> 01:06:28.393
I know who I am.

01:06:28.395 --> 01:06:29.893
Oh yeah?

01:06:29.895 --> 01:06:31.338
What did Paul want?

01:06:31.340 --> 01:06:32.171
He was just calling checking,

01:06:32.173 --> 01:06:34.105
see if you're being a good little wife?

01:06:36.155 --> 01:06:37.363
Yeah you must be really unhappy

01:06:37.365 --> 01:06:39.215
with this perfect real life you have.

01:06:40.055 --> 01:06:41.653
I wanted this.

01:06:41.655 --> 01:06:43.933
I wanted all of this, I
wanted a house, the pool,

01:06:43.935 --> 01:06:45.283
all the fancy toys.

01:06:45.285 --> 01:06:48.703
Is that all you care about,
this superficial bullshit?

01:06:48.705 --> 01:06:49.948
No, I care about you.

01:06:52.063 --> 01:06:53.588
I should have had you.

01:06:54.675 --> 01:06:56.125
We should have been together.

01:06:57.195 --> 01:06:59.858
But I made a choice, a decision.

01:07:02.445 --> 01:07:05.473
I thought it'd bring me
back here, back to you

01:07:05.475 --> 01:07:06.608
but it didn't.

01:07:07.585 --> 01:07:08.578
'Cause I failed.

01:07:10.555 --> 01:07:12.255
My parents knew, they always knew.

01:07:13.095 --> 01:07:15.733
That's why they threw me to the wolves.

01:07:15.735 --> 01:07:16.568
You knew.

01:07:17.695 --> 01:07:20.483
That's how you got here with Paul

01:07:20.485 --> 01:07:22.958
and all this.

01:07:23.805 --> 01:07:26.043
What's so great about this?

01:07:26.045 --> 01:07:28.833
You know at work, I'm fighting and clawing

01:07:28.835 --> 01:07:30.523
just to be heard.

01:07:30.525 --> 01:07:34.323
I even spent years trying to mold myself

01:07:34.325 --> 01:07:37.223
into this person and they
don't even listen to me.

01:07:37.225 --> 01:07:40.713
And Paul, half the time
he's not even here!

01:07:40.715 --> 01:07:42.559
And when he is,

01:07:42.561 --> 01:07:44.858
he doesn't see the real me.

01:07:48.924 --> 01:07:52.415
All this time, I've been
looking for something

01:07:53.885 --> 01:07:55.568
and I thought I found it in him.

01:07:57.375 --> 01:07:58.242
But I didn't.

01:08:05.585 --> 01:08:06.955
I'm not the same guy anymore.

01:08:08.524 --> 01:08:09.774
Not completely.

01:08:13.478 --> 01:08:15.868
This morning, I bathed in a lake.

01:08:17.805 --> 01:08:19.455
I stole food out of the dumpster.

01:08:21.103 --> 01:08:22.752
I can't even afford my own toothpaste.

01:08:26.385 --> 01:08:30.368
My drum and my car,
they're my whole world.

01:08:32.502 --> 01:08:34.578
I lost everything else
'cause I had to be me.

01:08:35.680 --> 01:08:39.919
You don't have to do it alone.

01:08:39.921 --> 01:08:40.997
I am alone.

01:08:40.999 --> 01:08:43.999
Not anymore, you don't have to be.

01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:48.332
No.

01:08:49.654 --> 01:08:51.593
We can't be together.

01:08:51.595 --> 01:08:54.183
How can we be together
knowing what you had to do,

01:08:54.185 --> 01:08:55.535
what you had to go through?

01:08:57.879 --> 01:08:59.629
It's been 10 years.

01:09:00.774 --> 01:09:02.692
I can't lose you again.

01:09:06.156 --> 01:09:07.988
I want to be with you.

01:09:25.741 --> 01:09:26.573
Fuck it.

01:09:51.450 --> 01:09:52.283
Now what?

01:10:02.238 --> 01:10:03.071
I don't know.

01:10:08.498 --> 01:10:13.498
♪ Didn't even see the
streetlight coming on ♪

01:10:16.098 --> 01:10:21.098
♪ Selling Thomas Dalley boulevard ♪

01:10:23.698 --> 01:10:28.698
♪ Oooh ♪

01:10:31.794 --> 01:10:33.711
♪ Oooh ♪

01:10:40.708 --> 01:10:43.103
This is all very complicated.

01:10:43.105 --> 01:10:43.938
It's easy.

01:10:45.253 --> 01:10:47.545
Maybe that's why
everything else is so hard.

01:10:47.547 --> 01:10:50.664
Loving you has always been easy.

01:10:50.666 --> 01:10:51.999
I do love you.

01:10:53.517 --> 01:10:57.616
♪ And I am not the first one ♪

01:10:57.618 --> 01:11:01.330
♪ Sure as hell won't be the last ♪

01:11:01.332 --> 01:11:05.296
♪ I was a different person ♪

01:11:05.298 --> 01:11:09.275
♪ When I cursed the glass ♪

01:11:09.277 --> 01:11:13.158
♪ And you'll take notice ♪

01:11:13.160 --> 01:11:17.236
♪ When I open up ♪

01:11:17.238 --> 01:11:21.238
♪ And pour myself in with you ♪

01:11:21.240 --> 01:11:26.240
♪ Oooh ♪

01:11:27.877 --> 01:11:29.794
♪ Oooh ♪

01:12:57.443 --> 01:12:59.276
Good morning.

01:13:00.386 --> 01:13:01.636
Good morning.

01:13:07.675 --> 01:13:08.738
Coffee?

01:13:08.740 --> 01:13:09.573
Oh, yes.

01:13:11.235 --> 01:13:12.066
- Which one?
- I don't care.

01:13:12.068 --> 01:13:13.543
- Okay.
- The fuller one.

01:13:13.545 --> 01:13:15.513
Take the blue pill.

01:13:15.515 --> 01:13:19.093
You know, you should be a housewife.

01:13:19.095 --> 01:13:19.995
You're good at it.

01:13:21.215 --> 01:13:24.283
